article.description: Jahmir Young registered 14 points and eight rebounds as Charlotte extended its home win streak to eight games, narrowly defeating UTEP 68-64 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Young scores 14 to lead Charlotte past UTEP 68-64
article.linkText: Young scores 14 to lead Charlotte past UTEP 68-64
article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- Jahmir Young registered 14 points and eight rebounds as Charlotte extended its home win streak to eight games, narrowly defeating UTEP 68-64 on Thursday night. Drew Edwards had 13 points for Charlotte (13-9, 7-4 Conference USA). Amidou Bamba added 11 points. Milos Supica had 10 points. Daryl Edwards scored a career-high 24 points for the Miners (13-11, 4-7). Souley Boum added 20 points. Charlotte takes on UTSA at home on Saturday. UTEP faces Old Dominion on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
